## 6. Coalition Type × Snare Cluster Cross-Tabulation (tangled_rope→snare)

Matched 594 of 594 tangled_rope→snare members to coalition types (0 unmatched — different rival type in decomposition).
Cluster threshold: P(snare) ≥ 0.5 = high-snare, P(snare) < 0.5 = low-snare.

### Contingency Table

| Coalition Type | Low-Snare | High-Snare | Total | % High-Snare |
|----------------|----------:|-----------:|------:|-------------:|
| uniform_tangled | 18 | 25 | 43 | 58.1% |
| institutional_dissent | 122 | 253 | 375 | 67.5% |
| analytical_dissent | 0 | 1 | 1 | 100.0% |
| split_field | 29 | 145 | 174 | 83.3% |
| other | 0 | 1 | 1 | 100.0% |
| **Total** | **169** | **425** | **594** | **71.5%** |

### Per-Coalition Descriptive Statistics

| Coalition Type | N | Mean | Median | Std | Min | Max |
|----------------|--:|-----:|-------:|----:|----:|----:|
| uniform_tangled | 43 | 0.5441 | 0.6252 | 0.3752 | 0.0007 | 0.9741 |
| institutional_dissent | 375 | 0.6398 | 0.8785 | 0.3853 | 0.0002 | 0.9915 |
| analytical_dissent | 1 | 0.7367 | 0.7367 | 0.0000 | 0.7367 | 0.7367 |
| split_field | 174 | 0.6740 | 0.6988 | 0.1753 | 0.0525 | 0.9931 |
| other | 1 | 0.8292 | 0.8292 | 0.0000 | 0.8292 | 0.8292 |

### Chi-Squared Test of Independence

- H0: Coalition type and snare cluster are independent
- Chi² = 19.5338, df = 4, p = 0.000617
- **Result: REJECT H0 at α=0.05** — coalition type and snare cluster are NOT independent

**Interpretation:**
The bimodal snare structure (low-snare vs high-snare clusters) is significantly associated with coalition type. Different coalition types have different propensities to fall into the low-snare vs high-snare cluster, confirming that the U-shaped Beta(0.64, 0.47) distribution reflects underlying coalition structure rather than random variation.
